This is the data importer, that will take .csv files and import them into our SQL server
The original importer has now been updated to use a relative path for accessing csv_files!


Credits to Malik Waters for creating the original importer.
Credits to Joshua Hwang for updating it.



Importers made in this order:
- import_cast.py
- import_movies.py              <look below>
- import_crew.py
- import_genres.py
- import_reviews.py (WIP, discontinued implementation for now, look at temp_calls file)

all store in a temp_xxx, xxx being the name of the .csv file



NOTE: You will need to put the csv files in the csv_files folder; it's too large to send it over GitHub!
Download the data through this link:
https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/rishabhkumar2003/the-movie-database-tmdb-comprehensive-dataset


